<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-06T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-06T14:00:00-05:00" n="785" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d785">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.512/1521: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-06T15:00:00-04:00">August 6, 1938—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>For the Ambassador. Reference Canton’s July 16, 11 a.m., in regard to
                            transit taxes. The Department assumes that you have made appropriate
                            representations to the Chinese Foreign Office.</p>
                        <p>Please inform Canton that the Department has not received the despatch
                            referred to in the telegram under reference.<note n="25" xml:id="d785fn25">The despatch (not printed) was received two days
                                later, August 8.</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>